HEADWORD: Bogwood
<hw>Bog"wood`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The wood of trees,
esp. of oaks, dug up from peat bogs. It is of a shining black or ebony
color, and is largely used for making ornaments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bogy</ent>⟦br⟧
